Exxon Says Worker Injured at Torrance Refinery Yesterday

-- B y   P a u l   B u r k h a r d t
-- 
2011-03-30T19:58:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/exxon-says-worker-injured-at-torrance-oil-refinery-yesterday.html
Exxon Mobil Corp. (XOM)  said a worker was
injured yesterday at its Torrance refinery in  California .  The worker was hurt while performing his duties and was
hospitalized, Aarti Ramachandran, a refinery spokeswoman, said
in a telephone interview.  “According to medical personnel, the employee’s injuries
are not considered life-threatening,” said Ramachandran. She
declined to comment on where the incident occurred and what
equipment may have been involved.  The 155,800-barrel-a-day plant is expected to meet
contractual obligations, she said.  The state Division of Occupational Safety and Health is
investigating the incident, said Krisann Chasarik, a spokeswoman
for the agency in  San Francisco . No further details were
available, she said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Burkhardt in  New York  at 
 pburkhardt@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Stets at 
 dstets@bloomberg.net . 